            },
            {
              "title": "Funding your innovation",
              "link": "https://innovation.nhs.uk/funding-your-innovation/"
            }
          ],
          "position": 3
        },
        {
          "title": "Blog: How to get your innovation adopted in the NHS: Advice from ...",
          "link": "https://www.sbrihealthcare.org/news/blog-how-to-get-your-innovation-adopted-in-the-nhs-advice-from-definition-health",
          "snippet": "Our innovation supports over 250,000 surgical patients across 10 NHS trusts. In our phase 2 SBRI Healthcare sustainability study at Sherwood ...",
          "date": "Dec 11, 2024",
          "position": 4
        },
        {
          "title": "The Small Business Research Initiative (SBRI) Healthcare programme",
          "link": "https://www.rand.org/pubs/research_reports/RR1828.html",
          "snippet": "RAND's divisions conduct research on a uniquely broad front for clients around the globe.\n\nThis study explores the contribution of the Small Business Research Initiative (SBRI) Healthcare programme to innovation in the NHS. It was commissioned by the UK Department of Health Policy Research Programme. The findings show that the SBRI Healthcare programme is providing effective support for small companies to develop innovations that address NHS needs, but further action is required to ensure the programme's development and uptake.\n\nAn evaluation of programme activities, outcomes and impacts\n",
          "date": "Oct 30, 2017",
          "position": 5
        }
      ]
    }
  }
]

